<TEXT>
when it comes to worms wayne fauser 
is all business even at the dinner table 
he stocks more than 10 million worms on his three adelaidebased 
farms for his company fauser all states worms pty ltd which has 
grown into one of the largest worm farms in the country since its 
1985 inception 
and at the risk of eating into his profits fauser also consumes 
worms in great quantity in sandwiches omelettes and just about 
any food that can contain meat 
theyre a great source of protein and they taste great he 
said monday as he snacked on an overflowing worm sandwich 
the worms must be fed a diet of dough for 48 hours before being 
cooked 
then theyre all right for all sorts of dishes fauser said 
im sure they will eventually be on adelaide menus 
as an easy meal he suggests dice and fry an onion in a frying 
pan add live worms and two cups of minced pork or beef fry until 
cooked add a can of tomatoes chopped red pepper salt and 
seasoning just before serving sprinkle with cheese the end 
result is a meal for two 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

