<TEXT>
a change in government style is promised for 
singapore when prime minister lee kuan yew a benevolent but stern 
patriarch steps aside after 31 robust years 
plans call for first deputy prime minister goh chok tong to take 
over later this year sometime after sept 16 when lee turns 67 
goh 48 was named to the no 2 post in 1985 using a 
consultative leadership style goh says he expects to preside over 
a more open society with the goal of making singapore a great 
small nation 
lee is not passing completely from the scene however and his 
influence is expected to remain intact goh intends to have him in 
the cabinet as a senior minister without portfolio 
those who believe that when i have left the government as 
prime minister that ive gone into permanent retirement really 
should have their heads examined he once told a gathering of his 
peoples action party 
even from my sick bed even if you are going to lower me into 
the grave and i feel that something is going wrong ill get up 
the cambridgeeducated lawyer took charge in 1959 modern 
singapore began its independent existence with no resources no 
industry bitter racial divisions and potentially unfriendly 
neighbors 
lee helped forge an identity for this polyglot place uniting 
with sizeable malay and indian minorities an ethnic chinese 
majority regarded with suspicion by its moslem neighbors in 
malaysia and indonesia 
he demanded discipline to overcome hardships obedience hard 
work cleanliness thrift and the profit motive all came into play 
as a shabby british colonial outpost was transformed 
now its a flourishing banking and commercial center with 
hightech industries firstclass education and glitzy shopping 
centers 
lees government enjoys a reputation for honesty efficiency and 
a strong sense of direction standards are high and there is a 
strict moral code tipping jaywalking littering discourtesy and 
failing to flush public toilets after use are officially denounced 
those suspected of more serious transgressions such as subversion 
and drug abuse 28 convicted traffickers have been hanged can 
expect no mercy 
in recent years lees dominance over national affairs has been 
largely accepted as the justifiable means to an end that benefited 
most singaporeans 
we decide what is right never mind what the people think 
he once said more than half singapores 27 million people were 
born during lees tenure and more than 80 percent have had no other 
leader during their adult lives 
those who would challenge that leadership found themselves 
subject to arrest detention without trial public humiliation and 
general harassment by a government reluctant to acknowledge dissent 
lee said several years ago that his political heirs sometimes 
did not seem tough enough to keep the opposition and other critics 
in their place he nevertheless planned an orderly transfer of 
power to a new generation 
in 1988 he admitted publicly that he preferred education 
minister tony tan instead of the easygoing goh as his successor 
tan did not aspire to the post 
goh told the party faithful in april that he stands for 
continuity not change but he also said he expects to run a more 
open administration offering participation accommodation and 
consensus 
participation means involving as many as practicable in the 
political process goh said painting a picture of a kinder 
gentler singapore he said participation involved understanding 
their hopes and aspirations their fears and tribulations and 
helping them to realize their hopes and overcome their fears 
more than just listening to their views i also want to give 
the people more opportunity to choose and decide for themselves 
instead of letting government agencies make most of the decisions 
that often have to be applied uniformly 
goh recently visited washington london and other capitals to 
introduce himself lee has been touring separately to say farewell 
to foreign friends and offer his views on the transition 
i could not get good men to join me if theyre going to hang 
around and wait for me to go senile lee said in london ive 
got a very competent and dedicated group fully able to run the 
country and in fact have been doing so for the last four years with 
minimal overview from me 
lee has accurately described his role as that of chairman of 
singapore inc a 240squaremile citystate run on corporate 
lines ministers act as executive directors largely untroubled by 
ideological issues or domestic political infighting they are 
chosen less for their electoral appeal than their capacity to 
manage a department effectively 
lees eldest son trade and industry minister lee hsien loong 
37 is already acknowledged by goh as his logical successor as 
prime minister 
