the southern baptist conventions phenomenal 
growth in the late 1960s and 70s dramatized the resurgence of 
religious conservatives 
now weakened by internal strife between moderates and 
fundamentalists the denomination that pledged in 1976 to reach 
every person in the world with the gospel of jesus christ by the 
year 2000 is struggling to hold its own 
the 149millionmember church grew by barely half a percent 
last year and experienced its first decline in foreign missionaries 
in nearly 20 years 
and even after 11 straight presidential victories by the 
fundamentalist wing the theological and political war rages over 
how to interpret the bible and share authority within the nations 
largest protestant denomination 
welcome to the battle of new orleans 1990 version is how 
convention spokesman alvin c shackleford greeted reporters at the 
denominations annual meeting 
more than 30000 delegates or messengers are expected for 
the threeday meeting opening today the presidential election was 
set for today 
