surge past the declining united methodist church as the nations 
secondlargest denomination behind the 55 millionmember roman 
catholic church 
but the churchs gain of 95000 members last year was a rise of 
only 64 percent the secondsmallest increase since 1936 
giving to denominational programs increased 189 percent to 
1373 million less than half the average 463 percent increase of 
the last five years and far lower than the 1039 percent increases 
throughout the 1970s 
and for the first time since 1972 the number of foreign 
missionaries declined dropping 87 to 3867 
the controversy that is blamed for the churchs decline dates to 
1979 when a group of fundamentalists concerned about liberal 
tendencies in the church began the first in a series of campaigns 
for control of the denomination 
the churchs moderate wing since has expressed increasing 
concerns it is being shut out in some cases the moderates have 
held back financial support 
the conservatives contend the bible is free from error even in 
its historical and scientific claims 
the moderates charge the fundamentalists are chipping away at 
