transit links and india agreed to reopen the border crossings by 
july 1 
today we have finally put an unfortunate interlude behind us 
and have fully normalized our relations singh told a news 
conference in announcing the agreement 
the agreement provides for concessions on customs duties for 
goods traded between the two countries and the dropping of 
restrictions on indian citizens seeking employment in nepal the 
two countries also agreed to consider their mutual security 
concerns 
