between an american president and an east german leader as an 
honor to the people of my country who won their freedom in a 
peaceful democratic revolution 
bush told white house visitors that the east german prime 
minister was clearly moved by his visit an event that would have 
been all but unthinkable at the height of the cold war 
he was so emotional about it he had never been here the 
president said describing his meeting with de maiziere as 
wonderful 
