as 100000 gallons of oil had spilled 
on monday mangan and other state officials urged lawmakers to 
unify the states scattershot approach to dealing with spills he 
said the state should prepare for such disasters the way san 
francisco prepares for earthquakes 
the focus has not been there there hasnt been any concerted 
effort to put such a contingency plan together mangan said 
