the nations most comprehensive law for preventing and cleaning up 
oil spills 
the law a compromise with oil shippers and retailers requires 
vessels and terminals to develop detailed spillresponse plans and 
terminals to buy spillcontainment equipment among other things 
it also raises liability limits for spill damage and cleanup costs 
for transporters and owners of cargo 
