last summer rebecca donovan landed her dream 
job as head librarian for hazens three schools 
she had spent 12 years in nearby stanton as an english teacher 
who also ran the school library arranged the prom and sold popcorn 
at basketball games 
i was pregnant at the end of the night my feet would be 
swelled up like bowling balls she said recalling those grim 
days of being spread too thin 
but her joy was brief donovan 37 got laid off in april 
north dakota cut its education budget by more than 31 million 
this spring after voters rejected tax increases and some schools 
closed others cut out art music and home economics and more than 
300 teachers lost their contracts 
donovans hopes of getting her job back may rest with north 
dakotas voters who decide today whether to raise the sales tax 
from 5 percent to 6 percent for a year to bail out education by 
raising an estimated 42 million 
john conrad a retired businessman who has campaigned to raise 
