give bush a new proprosal from gorbachev to break the deadlock over 
germanys military allegiance 
the sueddeutsche zeitung said gorbachev would agree to nato 
membership for a united germany if the western alliance made a 
clear decision to transform itself into a political alliance 
speaking of the may 30june 3 summit with bush gorbachev said 
as a whole i think huge results were achieved in washington 
toward limiting nuclear and conventional weapons 
all this has great meaning he said another practical 
step was taken to realize the idea of a nonviolent nonnuclear 
world there is difficult work ahead but the danger of the cold 
war has begun to recede he said 
gorbachev and bush signed agreements to eliminate the two sides 
chemical weapons and to reach a final accord this year to cut 
sharply their strategic nuclear weapons 
