president bushs term may mark the end of 
american industrial strength unless he adopts an economic policy 
that provides more assistance to develop new technologies a 
research group said tuesday 
rep mel levine dcalif chairman of rebuild america said the 
united states needs an industryled strategy with government 
cooperation and support to compete in the world market 
the next three years represent a critical turning point in 
economic history the group said in a report titled fiddling 
while us industry burns 
if president bush sides with the pragmatists america can 
remain a worldclass power for the foreseeable future the report 
said if he continues to allow the ideologues to dominate 
decisionmaking his term may mark the end of american industrial 
might 
rebuild america describes itself as a nonprofit bipartisan 
research group established to promote productive investment in 
people and industry 
the organization report was critical of bushs economic advisers 
chief of staff john sununu budget director richard darman and 
economic adviser michael boskin for what it called handsoff 
laissezfaire policies toward commercial ventures 
those policies it said have failed to produce sufficient 
commercial research and development close the investment gap with 
japan ensure continued us leadership in strategic industries 
protect the us manufacturing base and are keeping us the 
worlds largest debtor and increasingly dependent upon foreigners 
the report was written by lester thurow dean of the sloan 
school of management at the massachusetts institute of technology 
professor george lodge of harvard business school ed miller 
president of the national center for manufacturing sciences and 
rebuild america director fred branfman 
thurow who joined levine at a news conference the united 
states spends only onehalf as much per capita on plant and 
equipment as the japanese twothirds as much as the germans with 
those governments footing 50 percent of the research and 
development bill 
we have to spend equivalent amounts he said 
the administrations three proposals for closing the investment 
gap reduction of the federal budget deficit a capital gains tax 
cut and its family savings plan will do little to boost 
productive investment in the united states the report contended 
unless the administration changes its policies the report said 
the us could be a second or thirdrate industrial power in the 
year 2000 and president bush will be remembered as the herbert 
hoover of us industrial competitiveness 
hoover elected in 1928 was president during the stock market 
crash of 1929 and resulting collapse of the economy that led to the 
great depression 
