japan said tuesday it is willing to resume loans to 
peru if the south american nations new government shows 
willingness to deal with its serious economic and social problems 
the japanese ancestry of perus new president alberto fujimori 
has raised hopes of greater access to japanese aid fujimori said 
monday he hoped to visit tokyo before his scheduled july 28 
inauguration 
