presidential runoff election sunday was the top story in many 
japanese newspapers foreign ministry spokesman taizo watanabe 
extended the governments heartfelt congratulations to fujimori 
he noted that fujimori would be the first ethnic japanese to 
head a foreign government 
but at the same time the diplomacy and the relations between 
the two countries should not be swayed by such factors watanabe 
said 
peru was the largest recipient of japanese aid in latin america 
in cumulative terms until 1988 but dropped to fourthlargest after 
it defaulted on payments and japan cut off its yen credits 
fujimori faces widespread unemployment a 2000 percent 
inflation rate terrorism and extensive drug trafficking 
despite perus previous default if there is a willingness to 
cope and overcome those problems and explain to us in concrete 
manner what means they will take and if we are satisfied yes 
there is always a possibility of more loans watanabe told a news 
briefing 
