the congress of the russian federation proclaimed 
sovereignty on tuesday with a declaration that carried no legal 
force but pointed to a wish for greater independence from the 
soviet central government 
the union treaty mentioned several times in the declaration 
refers to a future voluntary agreement among soviet republics 
incorporating them into the country under newly negotiated terms 
it is not known when the treaty will be offered up for negotiating 
nor what its terms will be 
here are excerpts of the 15point declaration translated by the 
associated press 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the first congress of peoples deputies of the russian 
federation aware of its historical responsibility for the fate of 
russia testifying to its respect for the sovereign rights of all 
peoples united by the union of soviet socialist republics 
expressing the will of the people solemnly proclaims the state 
sovereignty of the russian soviet federative socialist republic on 
all its territory and declares its determination to create a 
democratic lawbased state in the framework of the renewed soviet 
union 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the russian soviet federative socialist republic is a sovereign 
state created by the peoples who united in it historically the 
sovereignty of the republic is a natural and necessary condition 
of the existence of the statehood of russia which has history 
culture and traditions of many centuries 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
in order to maintain the political economic and legal 
guarantees of sovereignty of the republic the full power of the 
republic is established for deciding all questions of 
governmental and public life except for those that are voluntarily 
given over to the soviet union including the priority of the 
russian constitution and the republics laws on all the 
territory of the republic the validity of acts of the soviet 
union that contradict the sovereign rights of the republic are 
suspended by the republic on its territory disagreements between 
the republic and the union are resolved according to a procedure 
set in the union treaty 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the republic reserves the right to freely secede from the 
ussr in a procedure established by the union treaty and the 
laws based on it 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
this declaration serves as the basis for working out a new 
russian constitution contracting the union treaty and perfecting 
republic laws 
