the west german newspaper sueddeutsche zeitung said monday that 
prime minister lothar de maiziere of east germany would carry a new 
gorbachev proposal to break the deadlock to a meeting with bush it 
said gorbachev would agree to nato membership for a united germany 
if the western alliance made a clear decision to transform itself 
into a political alliance 
gorbachev said tuesday of the summit as a whole i think huge 
results were achieved in washington toward limiting nuclear and 
conventional weapons 
all this has great meaning another practical step was taken 
to realize the idea of a nonviolent nonnuclear world 
he said hard work lies ahead but the cold war danger has begun 
to recede 
gorbachev and bush signed agreements to eliminate the two sides 
chemical weapons and to reach a final accord this year to cut 
deeply their strategic nuclear weapons 
