this nation simon said it is infinitely wrong in terms of the 
icc approval 
what we want to avoid is a situation where people come in and 
buy the railroad and then just dismember it he said 
sen j james exon dneb argued that republicans should put 
national interest over concerns with a favor for bush 
i hope that we can get back not to whats nice for the party 
but what is right for america he said overriding this veto is 
certainly right for america and its transportation needs 
in the house vote last week 58 republicans joined 236 democrats 
for the override the vote against was 123 it was the first 
successful override vote in either chamber in the bush 
administration however a successful override requires a 
twothirds majority in both chambers 
