audiences including shakespeares measure for measure and 
the tempest and arthur millers death of a salesman in 
which ying played willy loman 
in bernardo bertoluccis movie the last emperor filmed in 
china ying played the jailer who helps remold deposed emperor pu 
yi into a socialist citizen he also played mongol emperor kublai 
khan in the 1982 television miniseries marco polo produced by 
italy the united states japan and china 
yings dismissal was one of several highlevel personnel changes 
approved since may 18 by the state council chinas cabinet xinhua 
said it was the first time any of the changes have been disclosed 
