<TEXT>
southern baptists elected a fundamentalist 
minister president tuesday solidifying conservative control of the 
nations largest protestant denomination 
the rev morris chapman of wichita falls texas defeated the 
candidate backed by moderates the rev daniel vestal of the 
atlanta suburb of dunwoody the 21471to15753 vote gave chapman 
a 58 percent majority 
the convention moved toward curtailing funding for the 
washingtonbased baptist joint committee on public affairs which 
lobbies for religious freedom on behalf of nine baptist bodies 
fundamentalists have denounced the lobby for opposing organized 
prayer in public schools and for not opposing abortion 
the election outcome extended fundamentalist control for the 
12th straight year some moderates predicted they would give up 
trying to retake control of the 149 millionmember denomination 
some also said its national operations with a budget of more than 
440 million a year would lose much support from moderates 
chapman said at a postelection news conference that he would 
seek peace and harmony in the denomination but what we 
believe about the bible is nonnegotiable he said he has never 
advocated any wholesale housecleaning of those not accepting 
belief in an infallible bible 
nearly all southern baptists are theological conservatives 
devoted to the bibles authority but fundamentalists stress its 
inerrancy that it is without error in any way historically 
scientifically or religiously 
they also have imposed detailed questioning in denominational 
agencies and institutions to assure adherence of personnel to the 
expanded requirements 
the southern baptist presidency is one of the most powerful 
offices in us christianity with appointive powers controlling 
selection of governing trustees of a farflung network of agencies 
and institutions 
chapman said he would advocate attrition to get rid of staff 
members executives or seminary professors who could not subscribe 
to an inerrant bible he said he felt that in time they would 
find a home more in line with their convictions 
members of first baptist church in wichita falls where chapman 
has been pastor since 1979 said they think chapman is the kind of 
person who can mend the denominations rift 
i see him as someone that can play the role of a peacemaker 
so im excited about it said tom bacus 44 a deacon of the 
4000member church 
although some moderates including vestal are fundamentalist or 
literalist about the bible they leave room for other 
understandings under the baptist view of soul competence of the 
individual 
the rev jerry vines of jacksonville fla who is completing 
his term as president told the convention that some want to leave 
room for all in the denomination but thats too much room 
he said denominations that havent insisted on an infallible 
inerrant bible were bound for the garbage dump 
the convention approved a change recommended by the executive 
committee to turn over religious liberty concerns to the 
denominations christian life commission this was expected to lead 
wednesday to a vote to cut out 87 percent of southern baptist 
support or 365328 from the baptist joint committee on public 
affairs 
numerous speakers protested turning over lobbying to a 
commission concerned with morality and abandoning the joint 
committee 
henry green of cocoa fla pleaded that we maintain 
fellowship with other baptists saying it is unbilibal to 
railroad through this plan to destroy cooperation 
the campaigns for the presidency were intensified this time by 
added fundamentalist attacks on seminaries including the 
administration and some professors at the 131yearold flagship 
southern baptist theological seminary in louisville ky 
its president the rev roy honeycutt and the faculty have 
struck back calling accusations of doctrinal infidelity false 
distortions that sow seeds of hate 
chapman 49 a mississippi native got his theological education 
at southwester baptist theological seminary in fort worth texas 
he was pastor of churches in albuquerque nm and in waco and 
rogers texas before assuming his present pastorate at first 
baptist church in wichita falls texas 
vestal 46 the son of an evangelist also got his ministerial 
education at the fort worth seminary he previously led churches in 
arlington fort worth and midland texas before becoming pastor of 
dunwoody baptist church in suburban atlanta 
</TEXT>
