government report on agricultural supply and demand 
in the report which was released after the close the usda 
lowered its 1990 winter wheat producton forecast to 2089 billion 
bushels from last months projection of 2092 billion the number 
was slightly above market expections and still well above last 
years harvest of 1454 billion bushels 
