ahead of a report that showed a 304millionpound drawdown last 
week in supplies of frozen bellies in warehouses outside of 
chicago the reduction was larger than expected 
live cattle futures settled 30 cent lower to 08 cent higher 
with june at 7620 cents a pound feeder cattle were 48 cent lower 
