<DOCNO> AP900612-0257 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
a new york stock exchange panel tuesday proposed 
new severe trading halts to curb wild price swings but said widely 
criticized program trading strategies didnt cause market 
volatility 
the report capped a sixmonth study commissioned after the stock 
market plunged last october driving away many individual investors 
already shaken by the 1987 crash and provoking an outcry against 
program trading 
we need the small investor to feel he can go in and invest 
with confidence said general motors corp chairman roger smith 
chairman of the 19member market volatility and investor confidence 
panel 
the group proposed that the nyse install circuitbreakers to 
slow trading during wide market fluctuations the system would put 
a 400point cap on the possible daily rise or fall in the dow jones 
industrial average and the nations futures and options markets 
would coordinate trading halts 
but the panel found nothing inherently wrong with program 
trading the computerdriven strategy typically links the buying 
and selling of stock and stockindex futures and has been blamed 
for scaring away individual investors by feeding market plunges 
it suggested that program trading was a public relations problem 
for wall street and the perception that such strategies were unfair 
to individual investors or an abuse of the markets is largely 
unwarranted 
the panel was formed after the 190point plunge by the dow 
industrials last oct 13 which began with word that a takeover 
offer for the parent of united airlines had collapsed some experts 
have said that single event combined with speculative selling and 
program trading destabilized the market 
a type of program trading also has been blamed for worsening the 
black monday stock market crash of oct 19 1987 when the dow 
industrials fell 508 points since the crash the securities 
industry has been attempting to address questions about program 
trading in order to head off possibly restrictive moves by federal 
regulators or congress 
the nyse study concluded that market volatility and program 
trading are not the primary concern of individual investors who 
are more concerned about whether todays markets are operated 
fairly and honestly 
nonetheless it said the belief that program trading has 
diminished the fairness of markets reduces investor confidence 
among the nyse proposals 
a fourtier circuitbreaker coordinated among the us 
stock futures and options markets trading would stop for one hour 
when the dow jones average moves up or down 100 points from the 
previous days close 90 minutes when it moves 200 points and two 
hours each when it moves 300 points and 400 points 
the halts are longer than ones previously imposed by the big 
board they would require approval by the nyse chicago mercantile 
exchange and chicago board of trade 
revising federal securities laws to make it easier for 
corporations to buy back their own stock during market turmoil 
develop new products that would enable individual investors to 
protect themselves from extreme intraday price swings 
improve the exchanges ability to police intermarket trading 
abuses 
consolidating regulation of stocks and stockrelated futures 
under one federal agency to improve investor confidence similar 
legislation is being considered by congress 
the panel admitted that trading abuses exist in the financial 
markets but they do not appear to be embedded in the system in 
short the markets are not tilted against the individual investor 
or anyone else 
securities and exchange commission chairman richard s breeden 
said he was extremely pleased the panel endorsed creating a 
single regulatory agency for stocks and stockderived futures 
breeden said the report in essence fully confirms 
legislation backed by the bush administration that would give the 
sec authority over regulating stockindex futures 
in a dissent filed with the report chicago mercantile exchange 
chairman leo melamed a member of the panel opposed the 
singleregulator recommendation he said a majority of the panel 
simply mirrored a popular perception that consolidation of 
regulation seems desirable 
opponents of program trading criticized the report 
its simply an affirmaiton of the fact that the nyse has 
surrendered all of their hopes and dreams to the institutions 
said charles wohlstetter chairman of contel corp theyve 
accepted defeat without a fight 
in a survey of 560 people included in the report more than 50 
percent of respondents said they didnt pay much attention to the 
stock market or thought it was stable or pretty good 
more than half of the respondents said they hadnt heard of 
program trading but among people who own stock and were aware of 
the term 32 percent said program trading makes it hard for small 
investors to particpate in the stock market 
on a rating of concerns 58 percent of direct shareholders said 
their biggest concern was the honesty and ethics of stockbrokers 
compared to 18 percent for market volatility and 11 percent for 
program trading 
the big board defines program trading as any order for the 
simultaneous purchase or sale of 15 or more stocks index 
arbitrage a form of program trading involves rapid trading of 
stocks in new york and stockindex futures in chicago to profit 
from momentary price discrepancies 
empirical evidence suggests that index arbitrage is most 
likely the messenger through which new information gets 
incorporated into stock prices but it is not the primary cause of 
price changes the panel concluded 
without index arbitrage prices would still change albeit 
possibly more slowly with the arrival of new information it 
said 
nyse chairman john j phelan jr said the report would be voted 
on by the exchanges board and its recommendations discussed with 
other financial markets phelan said the he was confident the 
chicago futures markets would agree with most of the suggestions 
including the circuitbreakers 
the panel included officials from wall street major 
corporations state government and higher education 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

