<TEXT>
in another network attack on the current 
people meter ratings system nbc on tuesday announced its own 
plan for giving sponsors free ad time when its television shows get 
lowerthanpromised ratings 
nbc announcement made less than two weeks after a similar 
announcement by abc comes at a time the three networks are sharply 
disputing lower ratings reported by the vieweractivated 
peoplemeter ratings system of ac nielsen co 
although nielsen officials say last seasons reported drop in 
network viewing is real the networks argue that the nielsen data 
is wrong 
this has led nbc and abc to use different statistical formulas 
aimed at cushioning each network from financial losses caused by 
the data from peoplemeters which monitor viewing habits in 4000 
homes 
nbc officials have estimated their network could lose as much as 
100 million next season because of the lower ratings 
cbs expects to announce its own plan on wednesday said cbs 
research vice president david poltrack 
the planned changes could leave advertisers and their 
representatives facing three completely different network formulas 
for dealing with socalled makegood agreements with 
advertisers 
poltrack said he expected the strategy of advertising agencies 
then would be to voice a preference for one plan over the others 
and hope that that would bring the networks in conformance with one 
plan 
i think this will be resolved fairly quickly but i may be 
wrong he added 
the network announcements come at the onset of the socalled 
upfront buying period by advertisers for next season a period 
that can be worth 4 billion of the estimated 10 billion in total 
network sales for next season 
the matter has gotten a lot of publicity but its not that 
complicated said john sisk senior vice president for network 
negotiations at the j walter thompson advertising agency 
we negotiate a lot of things with them the networksthis 
will be part of the negotiations sisk said referring to the 
beginning upfront purchase of commercial time for the 199091 
season 
its a major part of the negotiations but only a part 
sisk said he hadnt yet seen the details of nbcs plan which 
bases its formula for makegoods on television audience data going 
back to 1982 
abcs plan uses a threeyear average starting in 1987 when 
nielsens peoplemeter system became the industrys national 
standard 
the system requires individual viewers in participating homes to 
log on to nielsen devices when watching a tv set the previous 
passive system simply recorded what was being watched but not who 
was watching 
richard kurlander whose company buys commercial time for 110 tv 
stations declined to comment on nbcs announcement until the 
network had provided him with its details 
obviously theres some unhappiness but itll get all sorted 
out said kurlander vice president of programming at petry 
television i think we should wait until we actually sift through 
it 
nbcs initial announcement was made in a corporate press release 
that among other things spoke of the use of a standard linear 
regression model in projecting television viewing levels for next 
season 
