<TEXT>
otto sturzenegger board chairman of the 
us subsidiary of the cibageigy pharmaceutical giant has died of 
cancer at age 64 the company announced 
sturzenegger died saturday in westchester county company 
spokesman tom chizmadia said 
sturzeneggers contributions to cibageigy corp the us 
branch of swissbased company have formed the foundation upon 
which this company has grown said richard barth president and 
executive officer of the us company 
cibageigy corp based in the westchester county town of 
ardsley produces pharmaceuticals agricultural chemicals 
plastics dyes and vision care products its 1989 sales were 35 
billion 
sturzenegger was the driving force behind our success over the 
last two decades barth said 
the swissborn executive began his career in 1952 in switzerland 
as a production chemist with the former jr geigy company two 
years later he moved to the united states and took charge of that 
companys manufacturing activities 
geigy merged with ciba in 1970 to form the cibageigy corp and 
sturzenegger was named its president and executive officer 
in 1978 he was named chairman of the board and in 1986 he 
retired as chief executive officer while retaining his title of 
chairman 
he also joined the board of directors of the parent company 
cibageigy ltd of basel switzerland 
sturzenegger had earned a bachelors degree in science from the 
federal institute of technology in zurich switzerland and 
masters and phd degrees in chemistry from oklahoma state 
university he also completed the advanced management program at 
harvard university 
sturzenegger also was a board member of the ncnb corp until 
april 1989 and was until his death a board member of a subsidiary 
of the international business machine corp that serves europe the 
middle east and africa 
